      "comment": "TORNADO ETHICS (1) is an accomplished sprinter with a great record at the short dashes. Kept coming to fill the minor placings over 400m at Maitland (22.33) in a Grade 4/5. Has a strong winning record here at the trip including three wins. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Deserves serious consideration. TINO BANNER (8) resumed in a NG at this track and ran into the frame when second over 324m (17.65). Solid record here at the distance winning six races. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to his credit. Will give a great sight again. HEAR ME ROAR (6) good effort to score last start by 0.8 lengths over 324m at this track in 17.72, beating Slick Razor. In form and in the mix.",
